Package: miCCI
Title: Charlson Comorbidity Index Estimation From Anonymised ICD-10-GM Codes
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Gaetan", "Kamdje Wabo",
           email = "gaetan.kamdjewabo@medma.uni-heidelberg.de",
           role  = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Piotr",  "Sokolowski", role = "aut"),
    person("Fabian", "Siegel",     role = "aut"))
Description: Five computational strategies for reconstructing the
    Charlson Comorbidity Index (CCI) from truncated (anonymised)
    three-character ICD-10-GM codes. S1 deterministic interval, S2
    inclusion-exclusion expected value, S3 multiple imputation, S4
    Bayesian Dirichlet posterior median, and a cross-validated Super
    Learner meta estimator (van der Laan, Polley and Hubbard 2007)
    that combines S1 to S4 via non-negative least squares. Reference
    population frequencies default to the German Federal Statistical
    Office table 23131-01 (Destatis), but any data.table of the same
    schema can be passed in. CCI mapping is the Quan et al. (2005)
    enhanced ICD-10 algorithm. This package provides the estimators
    only; downstream evaluation, bootstrap, and reporting are left
    to the user.
